         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0536">
               <p>Originally of <placeName>Rhyddlan, Flintshire</placeName>, Davies graduated from
                  Jesus College, <placeName>Oxford</placeName> in <date when="1759">1759</date> and
                  was ordained a priest in <date when="1760-01">January 1760</date>. He served as a
                  perpetual curate at <placeName>Bengeworth</placeName> from <date from="1767"
                     to="1772">1767–72</date>, where he once invited <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> to preach (JW, <hi
                     rend="italic">Journal</hi>, <date when="1768-03-17">Mar. 17, 1768</date>). In
                     <date when="1768">1768</date> Davies was also made rector of Coychurch,
                     <placeName>Glamorgan, Wales</placeName> (though he was infrequently resident
                  there). In <date when="1772">1772</date>
                  <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> sought to recruit
                  Davies as another ordained leader for the Methodist work in
                     <placeName>London</placeName>. This attempt provoked resentment among some lay
                  preachers, and was further soured by tensions between Davies and <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName>, leading to a parting of ways
                  in <date when="1774">1774</date>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
